    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It's an upstream bug with Python, which has been fixed in Python 3.2 (but not in the 2.x series).  There isn't anything we can do to fix it.  See http://bugs.python.org/issue10786\n\nIf you really need it to work, you can provide a custom `testRunner` to `unittest.main`:\n\n```\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    import sys\n    from unittest.runner import TextTestRunner\n    unittest.main(testRunner=TextTestRunner(stream=sys.stderr))\n```\n"
  },
